"title":{
"__html":"Diagnosis"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"523223",
"children":[
"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"116592",
"children":[
"The sickle cell syndromes can be diagnosed by hemoglobin electrophoresis."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"f088c1",
"children":[
"Most clinical findings in sickle cell disease are related to vaso-occlusion from sickled erythrocytes. Characteristic laboratory findings include elevated reticulocyte, platelet, and leukocyte counts and sickle cells on a peripheral blood smear."
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"1",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_hm_s14_inline_t1"
],
"forceOpen":true
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_hm_s14_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Treatment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"2ba996",
"children":[
"The three common disease-altering strategies are hydroxyurea therapy, prophylactic exchange transfusion, and ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"hematopoietic stem cell transplantation",
"children":[
"HSCT"
]
},
"."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"7b1f8d",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Hydroxyurea"
]
},
" is used for patients with three or more vaso-occlusive crises per year, for those with pain or chronic anemia interfering with daily activities, or those with recurrent acute chest syndrome. Additional approved agents for the treatment and prevention of painful events include L-glutamine and the P-selectin inhibitor crizanlizumab."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"d1e8d4",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Exchange transfusion"
]
},
" is indicated for patients with an acute stroke, fat embolism, or acute chest syndrome. Use prophylactic exchange transfusion for patients with a history of ischemic stroke."
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"bba7ff",
"children":[
"Because of transfusion-related complications, persons with sickle cell disease should not receive transfusion unless they have significant symptoms from their anemia or signs of end-organ failure (acute neurologic symptoms, acute chest syndrome, multiorgan failure). The transfusion target is hemoglobin level <10 g/dL (hemoglobin A level >70%). ",
{
"type":"alert",
"children":[
"Do not transfuse patients with simple vaso-occlusive pain."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"5ee48f",
"children":[
"Simple transfusion to a hemoglobin level of 10 g/dL has been shown to be equivalent to exchange transfusions in low- to medium-risk surgeries (e.g., adenoidectomy, inguinal hernia repair, cholecystectomy, joint replacement)."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"a1bb6a",
"children":[
"Erythropoietin is used for patients with severe anemia, low reticulocyte counts, and ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"chronic kidney disease",
"children":[
"CKD"
]
},
"."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"2",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_hm_f09"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"840d4e",
"children":[
"Hydroxyurea is contraindicated in pregnancy and kidney failure."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"d2882e",
"children":[
"Do not use meperidine to treat painful crises because the accumulation of the metabolite normeperidine can lead to seizures."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"fb5884",
"children":[
"Iron overload resulting from multiple transfusions may require chelation therapy."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
